Package ie.gmit.dip

Class AbstractFileParser<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.gmit.dip.AbstractFileParser<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - a generic type that defines the return type after parsing.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractParser<ParsableFile,​T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleFileParser
    public abstract class AbstractFileParser<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements AbstractParser<ParsableFile,​T>
    The class AbstractFileParser is an abstract base type which implements the AbstractParser interface and therefore must have methods associated with setting some input which is to be parsed, and subsequently parsing the input. As an abstract class, it is intended to form the base of a hierarchy of specialized FileParser types. Specifically, an AbstractFileParser is designed to take a ParsableFile type as input in methods from AbstractParser which it implements. Generic functionality (getters/setters) are all incorporated to manage any ParsableFile operations. The parse method which must be implemented by anything implementing the AbstractParser interface remains abstract in AbstractFileParser, and must be completely specified by any specialized sub-types of AbstractFileParser which inherit from it.
